der Zeit bis 1700 werden hier vollständig ediert und übersetzt, Personen und Wappen identifiziert. Fotografien aller erhaltenen Objekte sowie die Möglichkeit eines Zugriffs auf zusätzliches Bildmaterial in hoher Auflösung mittels QR-Code ergänzen die Texte. Link zum virtuellen Rundgang über den Stadtgottesacker in Halle (erstellt durch Ilja Claus): https://360grad-denkmale.de/virtuelle-rundgaenge/stadtgottesacker-halle/.  aBetween 1557 and 1590, the Stadtgottesacker in Halle, a prototype of a Protestant burial ground outside the city walls, was expanded into an architectural unity that in form and completeness has no parallel north of the Alps. The volume contains all the inscriptions prior to 1700 on tombs and on 90 burial vaults, edited and translated in their entirety, along with notes on coats of arms and referenced persons.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aInscriptions, GermanzGermanyzHalle an der Saale. 0aInscriptions, LatinzGermanyzHalle an der Saale. 0aTombszGermanyzHalle an der Saale. 4aGrabdenkmäler. 4aHalle (Saale). 4aInschriften. 4aSepulkralkultur. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aFunerary monuments.  aHalle (Saale).  ainscriptions.  asepulchral culture.1 aBettina, Schröder-Bornkampf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConny, Jakab, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIlja, Claus.1 aKatja, Pürschel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKrüger, Klaus, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part 